{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"What I want to talk to you about"},{"time":3000,"text":"is what we can learn from studying the genomes"},{"time":5000,"text":"of living people"},{"time":7000,"text":"and extinct humans."},{"time":9000,"text":"But before doing that,"},{"time":11000,"text":"I just briefly want to remind you about what you already know:"},{"time":14000,"text":"that our genomes, our genetic material,"},{"time":16000,"text":"are stored in almost all cells in our bodies in chromosomes"},{"time":19000,"text":"in the form of DNA,"},{"time":21000,"text":"which is this famous double-helical molecule."},{"time":24000,"text":"And the genetic information"},{"time":26000,"text":"is contained in the form of a sequence"},{"time":28000,"text":"of four bases"},{"time":30000,"text":"abbreviated with the letters A, T, C and G."},{"time":33000,"text":"And the information is there twice --"},{"time":35000,"text":"one on each strand --"},{"time":37000,"text":"which is important,"},{"time":39000,"text":"because when new cells are formed, these strands come apart,"},{"time":41000,"text":"new strands are synthesized with the old ones as templates"},{"time":44000,"text":"in an almost perfect process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47000,"text":"But nothing, of course, in nature"},{"time":49000,"text":"is totally perfect,"},{"time":51000,"text":"so sometimes an error is made"},{"time":53000,"text":"and a wrong letter is built in."},{"time":56000,"text":"And we can then see the result"},{"time":58000,"text":"of such mutations"},{"time":60000,"text":"when we compare DNA sequences"},{"time":62000,"text":"among us here in the room, for example."},{"time":65000,"text":"If we compare my genome to the genome of you,"},{"time":68000,"text":"approximately every 1,200, 1,300 letters"},{"time":72000,"text":"will differ between us."},{"time":74000,"text":"And these mutations accumulate"},{"time":76000,"text":"approximately as a function of time."},{"time":79000,"text":"So if we add in a chimpanzee here, we will see more differences."},{"time":82000,"text":"Approximately one letter in a hundred"},{"time":85000,"text":"will differ from a chimpanzee."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87000,"text":"And if you're then interested in the history"},{"time":89000,"text":"of a piece of DNA, or the whole genome,"},{"time":91000,"text":"you can reconstruct the history of the DNA"},{"time":94000,"text":"with those differences you observe."},{"time":96000,"text":"And generally we depict our ideas about this history"},{"time":100000,"text":"in the form of trees like this."},{"time":102000,"text":"In this case, it's very simple."},{"time":104000,"text":"The two human DNA sequences"},{"time":106000,"text":"go back to a common ancestor quite recently."},{"time":109000,"text":"Farther back is there one shared with chimpanzees."},{"time":113000,"text":"And because these mutations"},{"time":116000,"text":"happen approximately as a function of time,"},{"time":118000,"text":"you can transform these differences"},{"time":120000,"text":"to estimates of time,"},{"time":122000,"text":"where the two humans, typically,"},{"time":124000,"text":"will share a common ancestor about half a million years ago,"},{"time":128000,"text":"and with the chimpanzees,"},{"time":130000,"text":"it will be in the order of five million years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":133000,"text":"So what has now happened in the last few years"},{"time":135000,"text":"is that there are account technologies around"},{"time":137000,"text":"that allow you to see many, many pieces of DNA very quickly."},{"time":141000,"text":"So we can now, in a matter of hours,"},{"time":143000,"text":"determine a whole human genome."},{"time":146000,"text":"Each of us, of course, contains two human genomes --"},{"time":149000,"text":"one from our mothers and one from our fathers."},{"time":152000,"text":"And they are around three billion such letters long."},{"time":156000,"text":"And we will find that the two genomes in me,"},{"time":158000,"text":"or one genome of mine we want to use,"},{"time":160000,"text":"will have about three million differences"},{"time":163000,"text":"in the order of that."},{"time":165000,"text":"And what you can then also begin to do"},{"time":167000,"text":"is to say, \"How are these genetic differences"},{"time":169000,"text":"distributed across the world?\""},{"time":171000,"text":"And if you do that,"},{"time":173000,"text":"you find a certain amount of genetic variation in Africa."},{"time":177000,"text":"And if you look outside Africa,"},{"time":180000,"text":"you actually find less genetic variation."},{"time":183000,"text":"This is surprising, of course,"},{"time":185000,"text":"because in the order of six to eight times fewer people"},{"time":188000,"text":"live in Africa than outside Africa."},{"time":191000,"text":"Yet the people inside Africa"},{"time":194000,"text":"have more genetic variation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197000,"text":"Moreover, almost all these genetic variants"},{"time":199000,"text":"we see outside Africa"},{"time":201000,"text":"have closely related DNA sequences"},{"time":203000,"text":"that you find inside Africa."},{"time":205000,"text":"But if you look in Africa,"},{"time":207000,"text":"there is a component of the genetic variation"},{"time":210000,"text":"that has no close relatives outside."},{"time":213000,"text":"So a model to explain this"},{"time":216000,"text":"is that a part of the African variation, but not all of it,"},{"time":219000,"text":"[has] gone out and colonized the rest of the world."},{"time":223000,"text":"And together with the methods to date these genetic differences,"},{"time":227000,"text":"this has led to the insight"},{"time":229000,"text":"that modern humans --"},{"time":231000,"text":"humans that are essentially indistinguishable from you and me --"},{"time":234000,"text":"evolved in Africa, quite recently,"},{"time":237000,"text":"between 100 and 200,000 years ago."},{"time":241000,"text":"And later, between 100 and 50,000 years ago or so,"},{"time":245000,"text":"went out of Africa"},{"time":247000,"text":"to colonize the rest of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249000,"text":"So what I often like to say"},{"time":251000,"text":"is that, from a genomic perspective,"},{"time":253000,"text":"we are all Africans."},{"time":255000,"text":"We either live inside Africa today,"},{"time":258000,"text":"or in quite recent exile."},{"time":260000,"text":"Another consequence"},{"time":262000,"text":"of this recent origin of modern humans"},{"time":265000,"text":"is that genetic variants"},{"time":267000,"text":"are generally distributed widely in the world,"},{"time":269000,"text":"in many places,"},{"time":271000,"text":"and they tend to vary as gradients,"},{"time":274000,"text":"from a bird's-eye perspective at least."},{"time":278000,"text":"And since there are many genetic variants,"},{"time":280000,"text":"and they have different such gradients,"},{"time":283000,"text":"this means that if we determine a DNA sequence --"},{"time":286000,"text":"a genome from one individual --"},{"time":289000,"text":"we can quite accurately estimate"},{"time":291000,"text":"where that person comes from,"},{"time":293000,"text":"provided that its parents or grandparents"},{"time":295000,"text":"haven't moved around too much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298000,"text":"But does this then mean,"},{"time":300000,"text":"as many people tend to think,"},{"time":302000,"text":"that there are huge genetic differences between groups of people --"},{"time":305000,"text":"on different continents, for example?"},{"time":307000,"text":"Well we can begin to ask those questions also."},{"time":310000,"text":"There is, for example, a project that's underway"},{"time":313000,"text":"to sequence a thousand individuals --"},{"time":315000,"text":"their genomes -- from different parts of the world."},{"time":318000,"text":"They've sequenced 185 Africans"},{"time":321000,"text":"from two populations in Africa."},{"time":324000,"text":"[They've] sequenced approximately equally [as] many people"},{"time":327000,"text":"in Europe and in China."},{"time":330000,"text":"And we can begin to say how much variance do we find,"},{"time":333000,"text":"how many letters that vary"},{"time":336000,"text":"in at least one of those individual sequences."},{"time":339000,"text":"And it's a lot: 38 million variable positions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343000,"text":"But we can then ask: Are there any absolute differences"},{"time":346000,"text":"between Africans and non-Africans?"},{"time":348000,"text":"Perhaps the biggest difference"},{"time":350000,"text":"most of us would imagine existed."},{"time":352000,"text":"And with absolute difference --"},{"time":354000,"text":"and I mean a difference"},{"time":356000,"text":"where people inside Africa at a certain position,"},{"time":359000,"text":"where all individuals -- 100 percent -- have one letter,"},{"time":362000,"text":"and everybody outside Africa has another letter."},{"time":366000,"text":"And the answer to that, among those millions of differences,"},{"time":369000,"text":"is that there is not a single such position."},{"time":374000,"text":"This may be surprising."},{"time":376000,"text":"Maybe a single individual is misclassified or so."},{"time":379000,"text":"So we can relax the criterion a bit"},{"time":381000,"text":"and say: How many positions do we find"},{"time":383000,"text":"where 95 percent of people in Africa have"},{"time":385000,"text":"one variant,"},{"time":387000,"text":"95 percent another variant,"},{"time":389000,"text":"and the number of that is 12."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391000,"text":"So this is very surprising."},{"time":393000,"text":"It means that when we look at people"},{"time":395000,"text":"and see a person from Africa"},{"time":398000,"text":"and a person from Europe or Asia,"},{"time":401000,"text":"we cannot, for a single position in the genome with 100 percent accuracy,"},{"time":405000,"text":"predict what the person would carry."},{"time":407000,"text":"And only for 12 positions"},{"time":409000,"text":"can we hope to be 95 percent right."},{"time":413000,"text":"This may be surprising,"},{"time":415000,"text":"because we can, of course, look at these people"},{"time":417000,"text":"and quite easily say where they or their ancestors came from."},{"time":421000,"text":"So what this means now"},{"time":423000,"text":"is that those traits we then look at"},{"time":425000,"text":"and so readily see --"},{"time":427000,"text":"facial features, skin color, hair structure --"},{"time":430000,"text":"are not determined by single genes with big effects,"},{"time":434000,"text":"but are determined by many different genetic variants"},{"time":437000,"text":"that seem to vary in frequency"},{"time":439000,"text":"between different parts of the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441000,"text":"There is another thing with those traits"},{"time":444000,"text":"that we so easily observe in each other"},{"time":447000,"text":"that I think is worthwhile to consider,"},{"time":449000,"text":"and that is that, in a very literal sense,"},{"time":452000,"text":"they're really on the surface of our bodies."},{"time":455000,"text":"They are what we just said --"},{"time":457000,"text":"facial features, hair structure, skin color."},{"time":460000,"text":"There are also a number of features"},{"time":462000,"text":"that vary between continents like that"},{"time":464000,"text":"that have to do with how we metabolize food that we ingest,"},{"time":468000,"text":"or that have to do"},{"time":470000,"text":"with how our immune systems deal with microbes"},{"time":473000,"text":"that try to invade our bodies."},{"time":475000,"text":"But so those are all parts of our bodies"},{"time":477000,"text":"where we very directly interact with our environment,"},{"time":480000,"text":"in a direct confrontation, if you like."},{"time":484000,"text":"It's easy to imagine"},{"time":486000,"text":"how particularly those parts of our bodies"},{"time":488000,"text":"were quickly influenced by selection from the environment"},{"time":491000,"text":"and shifted frequencies of genes"},{"time":493000,"text":"that are involved in them."},{"time":495000,"text":"But if we look on other parts of our bodies"},{"time":498000,"text":"where we don't directly interact with the environment --"},{"time":500000,"text":"our kidneys, our livers, our hearts --"},{"time":503000,"text":"there is no way to say,"},{"time":505000,"text":"by just looking at these organs,"},{"time":507000,"text":"where in the world they would come from."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511000,"text":"So there's another interesting thing"},{"time":513000,"text":"that comes from this realization"},{"time":516000,"text":"that humans have a recent common origin in Africa,"},{"time":520000,"text":"and that is that when those humans emerged"},{"time":523000,"text":"around 100,000 years ago or so,"},{"time":525000,"text":"they were not alone on the planet."},{"time":527000,"text":"There were other forms of humans around,"},{"time":530000,"text":"most famously perhaps, Neanderthals --"},{"time":533000,"text":"these robust forms of humans,"},{"time":535000,"text":"compared to the left here"},{"time":537000,"text":"with a modern human skeleton on the right --"},{"time":541000,"text":"that existed in Western Asia and Europe"},{"time":544000,"text":"since several hundreds of thousands of years."},{"time":546000,"text":"So an interesting question is,"},{"time":548000,"text":"what happened when we met?"},{"time":550000,"text":"What happened to the Neanderthals?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":552000,"text":"And to begin to answer such questions,"},{"time":554000,"text":"my research group -- since over 25 years now --"},{"time":558000,"text":"works on methods to extract DNA"},{"time":560000,"text":"from remains of Neanderthals"},{"time":562000,"text":"and extinct animals"},{"time":564000,"text":"that are tens of thousands of years old."},{"time":567000,"text":"So this involves a lot of technical issues"},{"time":570000,"text":"in how you extract the DNA,"},{"time":572000,"text":"how you convert it to a form you can sequence."},{"time":575000,"text":"You have to work very carefully"},{"time":577000,"text":"to avoid contamination of experiments"},{"time":580000,"text":"with DNA from yourself."},{"time":583000,"text":"And this then, in conjunction with these methods"},{"time":586000,"text":"that allow very many DNA molecules to be sequenced very rapidly,"},{"time":590000,"text":"allowed us last year"},{"time":592000,"text":"to present the first version of the Neanderthal genome,"},{"time":595000,"text":"so that any one of you"},{"time":597000,"text":"can now look on the Internet, on the Neanderthal genome,"},{"time":599000,"text":"or at least on the 55 percent of it"},{"time":602000,"text":"that we've been able to reconstruct so far."},{"time":605000,"text":"And you can begin to compare it to the genomes"},{"time":607000,"text":"of people who live today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610000,"text":"And one question"},{"time":612000,"text":"that you may then want to ask"},{"time":614000,"text":"is, what happened when we met?"},{"time":616000,"text":"Did we mix or not?"},{"time":618000,"text":"And the way to ask that question"},{"time":620000,"text":"is to look at the Neanderthal that comes from Southern Europe"},{"time":623000,"text":"and compare it to genomes"},{"time":625000,"text":"of people who live today."},{"time":627000,"text":"So we then look"},{"time":629000,"text":"to do this with pairs of individuals,"},{"time":631000,"text":"starting with two Africans,"},{"time":633000,"text":"looking at the two African genomes,"},{"time":635000,"text":"finding places where they differ from each other,"},{"time":638000,"text":"and in each case ask: What is a Neanderthal like?"},{"time":641000,"text":"Does it match one African or the other African?"},{"time":644000,"text":"We would expect there to be no difference,"},{"time":647000,"text":"because Neanderthals were never in Africa."},{"time":649000,"text":"They should be equal, have no reason to be closer"},{"time":652000,"text":"to one African than another African."},{"time":655000,"text":"And that's indeed the case."},{"time":657000,"text":"Statistically speaking, there is no difference"},{"time":659000,"text":"in how often the Neanderthal matches one African or the other."},{"time":663000,"text":"But this is different"},{"time":665000,"text":"if we now look at the European individual and an African."},{"time":669000,"text":"Then, significantly more often,"},{"time":672000,"text":"does a Neanderthal match the European"},{"time":674000,"text":"rather than the African."},{"time":676000,"text":"The same is true if we look at a Chinese individual"},{"time":679000,"text":"versus an African,"},{"time":681000,"text":"the Neanderthal will match the Chinese individual more often."},{"time":685000,"text":"This may also be surprising"},{"time":687000,"text":"because the Neanderthals were never in China."}]},{"cues":[{"time":689000,"text":"So the model we've proposed to explain this"},{"time":693000,"text":"is that when modern humans came out of Africa"},{"time":695000,"text":"sometime after 100,000 years ago,"},{"time":698000,"text":"they met Neanderthals."},{"time":700000,"text":"Presumably, they did so first in the Middle East,"},{"time":703000,"text":"where there were Neanderthals living."},{"time":705000,"text":"If they then mixed with each other there,"},{"time":707000,"text":"then those modern humans"},{"time":709000,"text":"that became the ancestors"},{"time":711000,"text":"of everyone outside Africa"},{"time":713000,"text":"carried with them this Neanderthal component in their genome"},{"time":716000,"text":"to the rest of the world."},{"time":718000,"text":"So that today, the people living outside Africa"},{"time":721000,"text":"have about two and a half percent of their DNA"},{"time":724000,"text":"from Neanderthals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726000,"text":"So having now a Neanderthal genome"},{"time":729000,"text":"on hand as a reference point"},{"time":731000,"text":"and having the technologies"},{"time":733000,"text":"to look at ancient remains"},{"time":735000,"text":"and extract the DNA,"},{"time":737000,"text":"we can begin to apply them elsewhere in the world."},{"time":741000,"text":"And the first place we've done that is in Southern Siberia"},{"time":744000,"text":"in the Altai Mountains"},{"time":746000,"text":"at a place called Denisova,"},{"time":748000,"text":"a cave site in this mountain here,"},{"time":750000,"text":"where archeologists in 2008"},{"time":753000,"text":"found a tiny little piece of bone --"},{"time":755000,"text":"this is a copy of it --"},{"time":757000,"text":"that they realized came from the last phalanx"},{"time":761000,"text":"of a little finger of a pinky of a human."},{"time":764000,"text":"And it was well enough preserved"},{"time":766000,"text":"so we could determine the DNA from this individual,"},{"time":769000,"text":"even to a greater extent"},{"time":771000,"text":"than for the Neanderthals actually,"},{"time":773000,"text":"and start relating it to the Neanderthal genome"},{"time":775000,"text":"and to people today."},{"time":778000,"text":"And we found that this individual"},{"time":780000,"text":"shared a common origin for his DNA sequences"},{"time":783000,"text":"with Neanderthals around 640,000 years ago."},{"time":787000,"text":"And further back, 800,000 years ago"},{"time":790000,"text":"is there a common origin"},{"time":792000,"text":"with present day humans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":794000,"text":"So this individual comes from a population"},{"time":796000,"text":"that shares an origin with Neanderthals,"},{"time":799000,"text":"but far back and then have a long independent history."},{"time":802000,"text":"We call this group of humans,"},{"time":804000,"text":"that we then described for the first time"},{"time":806000,"text":"from this tiny, tiny little piece of bone,"},{"time":808000,"text":"the Denisovans,"},{"time":810000,"text":"after this place where they were first described."},{"time":813000,"text":"So we can then ask for Denisovans"},{"time":816000,"text":"the same things as for the Neanderthals:"},{"time":818000,"text":"Did they mix with ancestors of present day people?"},{"time":822000,"text":"If we ask that question,"},{"time":824000,"text":"and compare the Denisovan genome"},{"time":826000,"text":"to people around the world,"},{"time":828000,"text":"we surprisingly find"},{"time":830000,"text":"no evidence of Denisovan DNA"},{"time":832000,"text":"in any people living even close to Siberia today."},{"time":837000,"text":"But we do find it in Papua New Guinea"},{"time":839000,"text":"and in other islands in Melanesia and the Pacific."},{"time":843000,"text":"So this presumably means"},{"time":845000,"text":"that these Denisovans had been more widespread in the past,"},{"time":848000,"text":"since we don't think that the ancestors of Melanesians"},{"time":851000,"text":"were ever in Siberia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":853000,"text":"So from studying"},{"time":855000,"text":"these genomes of extinct humans,"},{"time":858000,"text":"we're beginning to arrive at a picture of what the world looked like"},{"time":861000,"text":"when modern humans started coming out of Africa."},{"time":864000,"text":"In the West, there were Neanderthals;"},{"time":867000,"text":"in the East, there were Denisovans --"},{"time":869000,"text":"maybe other forms of humans too"},{"time":871000,"text":"that we've not yet described."},{"time":873000,"text":"We don't know quite where the borders between these people were,"},{"time":876000,"text":"but we know that in Southern Siberia,"},{"time":878000,"text":"there were both Neanderthals and Denisovans"},{"time":880000,"text":"at least at some time in the past."},{"time":883000,"text":"Then modern humans emerged somewhere in Africa,"},{"time":886000,"text":"came out of Africa, presumably in the Middle East."},{"time":889000,"text":"They meet Neanderthals, mix with them,"},{"time":892000,"text":"continue to spread over the world,"},{"time":895000,"text":"and somewhere in Southeast Asia,"},{"time":898000,"text":"they meet Denisovans and mix with them"},{"time":900000,"text":"and continue on out into the Pacific."},{"time":903000,"text":"And then these earlier forms of humans disappear,"},{"time":906000,"text":"but they live on a little bit today"},{"time":909000,"text":"in some of us --"},{"time":911000,"text":"in that people outside of Africa have two and a half percent of their DNA"},{"time":914000,"text":"from Neanderthals,"},{"time":916000,"text":"and people in Melanesia"},{"time":918000,"text":"actually have an additional five percent approximately"},{"time":921000,"text":"from the Denisovans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":924000,"text":"Does this then mean that there is after all"},{"time":926000,"text":"some absolute difference"},{"time":928000,"text":"between people outside Africa and inside Africa"},{"time":931000,"text":"in that people outside Africa"},{"time":933000,"text":"have this old component in their genome"},{"time":935000,"text":"from these extinct forms of humans,"},{"time":937000,"text":"whereas Africans do not?"},{"time":939000,"text":"Well I don't think that is the case."},{"time":942000,"text":"Presumably, modern humans"},{"time":944000,"text":"emerged somewhere in Africa."},{"time":946000,"text":"They spread across Africa also, of course,"},{"time":949000,"text":"and there were older, earlier forms of humans there."},{"time":952000,"text":"And since we mixed elsewhere,"},{"time":954000,"text":"I'm pretty sure that one day,"},{"time":956000,"text":"when we will perhaps have a genome"},{"time":958000,"text":"of also these earlier forms in Africa,"},{"time":960000,"text":"we will find that they have also mixed"},{"time":962000,"text":"with early modern humans in Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":966000,"text":"So to sum up,"},{"time":968000,"text":"what have we learned from studying genomes"},{"time":970000,"text":"of present day humans"},{"time":972000,"text":"and extinct humans?"},{"time":974000,"text":"We learn perhaps many things,"},{"time":976000,"text":"but one thing that I find sort of important to mention"},{"time":981000,"text":"is that I think the lesson is that we have always mixed."},{"time":984000,"text":"We mixed with these earlier forms of humans,"},{"time":986000,"text":"wherever we met them,"},{"time":988000,"text":"and we mixed with each other ever since."}]},{"cues":[{"time":992000,"text":"Thank you for your attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":994000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}